X-WR-CALNAME:Jubilee disruption
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/?Input=&lineIds=&dateTypeSelect=Future%20date&direction=&startDate=2026-06-01T23:00:00&endDate=2026-06-02T22:59:00">Disruption map.</a>\n\nTUBE STRIKE: Some London Underground Tube drivers are planning to take two full days of strike action on Tuesday 2 and Thursday 4 June.  During the strike\, no service is expected on the Circle line\, Piccadilly line\, the Metropolitan line between Baker Street and Aldgate\, and the Central line between White City and Liverpool Street. Service is expected across other Tube lines on both days. However\, there will be disruption to journeys and service levels will vary across the London Underground network. On both days\, there will be limited service before 0630 and customers should complete their journeys by 2100. Normal service expected on Monday 1 June\, Wednesday 3 June and Friday 5 June
DTEND:20260602T225900Z
DTSTART:20260601T230000Z
SUMMARY:Jubilee: Special Service
UID:09ce2faf-55f0-43d6-b258-1b2c713999ec@09ce.org
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/?Input=&lineIds=&dateTypeSelect=Future%20date&direction=&startDate=2026-06-01T05:45:30&endDate=2026-06-02T00:29:00">Disruption map.</a>\n\nJubilee Line: No service between Finchley Road and Waterloo and SEVERE DELAYS on the rest of the line while we fix a signal failure at Green Park. Tickets are being accepted on London Buses\, Mildmay line\, DLR\, Elizabeth line\, C2C\, Thameslink and Southeastern. 
